This paper deals with the combination of compressive sensing and particle filtering for dynamical systems. The paper discusses the use of nonlinear compressive sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of the Kalman filter, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with the estimation of state variables, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the estimation of state variables in nonlinear systems, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
